# PART 3 — Company Admin's First Login (tenant_admin)

**Frontend:** `http://localhost:5173/login`. Three steps: email → company code (the
`slug` you picked when onboarding, e.g. `zenith-logistics`) → password.

**What fires:**
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "admin@zenithlogistics.com", "password": "Zx9#kLp2mQ8r", "tenantSlug": "zenith-logistics" }
```
Response: `{ accessToken, refreshToken, expiresIn, tokenType }`. Then the frontend
calls `GET /api/v1/auth/me` (returns `{id, email, tenantId, role, isActive, workerId}`)
and `GET /api/v1/users/me` (returns `firstName`/`lastName` for display) to build the
session.

There is no setup wizard. You land straight on **`/dashboard`** (the general-purpose
dashboard — total employees, active/suspended/inactive counts, recent hires).

**What to actually do first, in order:**

1. **Organisation → Legal Entities** (`/organisation/legal-entities`) → **Add Legal
   Entity**. Fill name, country, tax ID, address. This is the *only* org-structure step
   that's real — do this before adding employees or creating pay runs, both of which
   reference a legal entity.
   ```
   POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/legal-entities
   Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
   { "name": "Zenith Logistics Nigeria", "country": "NG", "taxId": "RC-445566", "address": "12 Marina, Lagos" }
   ```
2. **Settings → Users & Roles** (`/settings/users`) → **Add User**. Create your HR
   Manager, Payroll Manager, Finance Manager, etc. here — same
   `POST /api/v1/users` call as the platform admin's "Add User," just scoped to your
   own tenant automatically (no tenant ID needed in the body — it comes from your JWT).
   ```
   POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
   Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
   { "email": "amaka@zenithlogistics.com", "password": "Hr9$Temp22aQ", "firstName": "Amaka", "lastName": "Eze", "role": "hr_manager" }
   ```
   Tell Amaka her temporary password directly — again, no invite email exists.
3. Now hand off to HR (Part 4) to start adding employees.

