# PART 5 — Password & Account Reality, Restated

- **Nobody resets their own password from a logged-out state.** If you're locked out,
  someone with `tenant_admin`/`super_admin` (or a platform admin, for platform users)
  has to create you a *fresh* account, or someone with direct database access has to
  intervene. There is no email-based recovery anywhere in this system today.
- **Changing your own password while logged in** works for everyone, any role:
  `PATCH /v1/users/me/password` with `{ currentPassword, newPassword }` (tenant users)
  or `PATCH /platform/users/me/password` (platform users).
- **Nobody signs themselves up.** Every account — platform or tenant — is created by
  someone else calling a `POST .../users` endpoint with a password they chose.

